history.content:
I'm a rising senior with a Phase 1 enrollment time of 1:30pm today. Next semester is my last semester as I only need 3 more CS classes to graduate. I was planning on enrolling in CS168 (in addition to 162 & 188), but it looks like there's no more reserved seats for LSCS majors and the waitlist is currently at 209. This is my #1 CS upper div course that I've wanted to take since declaring, so I'm not really interested in various other upper divs being offered other than the 3 I had planned to take.

I'm wondering if I Phase 1 this course will it be possible for me to make it into the class? And/or is there someone I can speak to about waitlist processing priority for graduating seniors if this is going to be my final semester at Cal?

Any advice would be appreciated, thanks!
history.subject: Will I be able to get into CS168?
